What you need to know:

Early enough in 1960, settlers laughed at Michael Blundell – one of the most respected settlers in Kenya – for saying in a meeting at City Hall, that the settlers could farm alongside locals in a multi-racial nation.December 12, 1963, and as the Duke of Edinburg handed instruments of independence to Jomo Kenyatta, the new Prime Minister undertook to improve living standards, uplift health facilities and eradicate illiteracy.